2ï¸âƒ£ GenServer.call(pid, message)
What it is

OTP abstraction

Built on top of send/receive

Implements requestâ€“response

Example
GenServer.call(pid, {:get_state})

What happens internally

Sends a message to the GenServer

Caller blocks

GenServer processes message

GenServer sends a reply

Caller resumes

Key properties

ğŸ”¹ Synchronous

ğŸ”¹ Guarantees a reply (or timeout)

ğŸ”¹ Safer for shared state access

ğŸ”¹ Handles timeouts & failures

When to use

Reading state

Updating state and needing confirmation

Business logic that depends on result

Rails analogy

Like calling a service object and waiting for the return value.

