5ï¸âƒ£ How to choose (INTERVIEW ANSWER)

I use GenServer.call when I need a reliable response or state consistency, and GenServer.cast or send for asynchronous events where I donâ€™t need a reply.

6ï¸âƒ£ Common follow-up questions (with answers)
â“ Can GenServer.call block forever?

No, it has a configurable timeout. If the GenServer doesnâ€™t reply, the caller exits.

â“ Why not always use send?

Because it lacks structure, error handling, and reply guarantees. OTP abstractions make systems safer and easier to maintain.

